489
00:26:47.710 --> 00:26:49.370
Oh.come on.guys.shawn.stay.

490
00:26:49.650 --> 00:26:50.750
Your case will still be there.

491
00:26:50.760 --> 00:26:53.080
Uh.the sooner we can crack 
this case and move on.

492
00:26:53.090 --> 00:26:54.330
the better.believe me.

493
00:26:54.770 --> 00:26:59.080
Well.this wouldn't have anything to do with
the wispy sunny pines suicide.now.would it?

494
00:27:00.470 --> 00:27:01.750
- No.
- Yes.sir.

495
00:27:03.890 --> 00:27:05.610
ooh.the plot thickens.

496
00:27:05.620 --> 00:27:06.970
Okay.it's true.

497
00:27:06.980 --> 00:27:07.740
Fine.

498
00:27:07.750 --> 00:27:09.170
And it hits a little close to home.

499
00:27:09.180 --> 00:27:11.440
seeing as how we were actually
there the first time it happened.

500
00:27:12.530 --> 00:27:13.920
the first time what happened?

501
00:27:17.450 --> 00:27:19.550
Did you open your eyes?

502
00:27:20.280 --> 00:27:21.800
Dad.you've known me my whole life.

503
00:27:21.810 --> 00:27:23.170
Of course I opened my eyes.

504
00:27:23.180 --> 00:27:26.380
Shawn.that is exactly why I refused
to let you ride around with me.

505
00:27:26.390 --> 00:27:27.970
Dad.let it go.I was nine.

506
00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:29.490
That is a lack of respect.

507
00:27:29.500 --> 00:27:30.560
Of protocol.

508
00:27:30.570 --> 00:27:31.580
Of protocol?

509
00:27:31.590 --> 00:27:33.630
Again.can I plead nine years old?

510
00:27:38.890 --> 00:27:41.720
And you guys.you've been freaked
out about this your entire lives?

511
00:27:41.730 --> 00:27:43.100
I don't even drive by that place.

512
00:27:45.240 --> 00:27:46.680
I really don't think it's funny.

513
00:27:46.690 --> 00:27:49.240
It was a very scary
thing for two young boys.

514
00:27:50.110 --> 00:27:52.250
Certainly puts a new spin
on the nanny in the omen.

515
00:27:52.260 --> 00:27:53.200
You know that's right.

516
00:27:53.210 --> 00:27:55.310
Shawn.how much did you see?

517
00:27:56.750 --> 00:27:58.180
You know.we didn'T.

518
00:27:58.190 --> 00:28:00.550
we didn't actually see.it.

519
00:28:00.630 --> 00:28:02.570
Luckily.he missed the bitter.grisly end.

520
00:28:02.580 --> 00:28:03.750
Luckily?

521
00:28:03.760 --> 00:28:04.680
Yes.luckily.

522
00:28:04.690 --> 00:28:05.960
I covered his eyes.but.

523
00:28:05.970 --> 00:28:07.190
we know what happened.

524
00:28:07.970 --> 00:28:08.850
I beg to differ.

525
00:28:08.860 --> 00:28:13.890
I think that you two missed one
very small but important detail.

526
00:28:17.890 --> 00:28:19.900
She never jumped.

527
00:28:21.910 --> 00:28:23.040
What?

528
00:28:23.280 --> 00:28:25.120
No.No.no.no.no.that'S.

529
00:28:25.550 --> 00:28:26.260
that's impossible.

530
00:28:26.270 --> 00:28:28.130
We saw the window.She was gone.

531
00:28:28.940 --> 00:28:32.460
because one off-duty police
officer pulled her back inside.

532
00:28:37.660 --> 00:28:40.650
"Scary" sherry craddock
was rehabilitated.

533
00:28:40.660 --> 00:28:42.650
I'm pretty sure that she's
married and living in fresno.

534
00:28:42.660 --> 00:28:45.290
Come on.guys.give
me some more credit here.

535
00:28:45.930 --> 00:28:50.840
I have no idea how that ridiculous urban
legend got started in the first place.

536
00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:57.390
Your big-ass mouth.

537
00:28:57.400 --> 00:28:58.770
I wanted to keep it a secret.

538
00:28:58.780 --> 00:29:00.800
You're the one who was
broadcasting it at the lunch table.

539
00:29:02.860 --> 00:29:03.740
I can't believe this.

540
00:29:03.750 --> 00:29:05.530
We actually started an urban legend.

541
00:29:05.540 --> 00:29:06.630
That's dope!

542
00:29:08.740 --> 00:29:12.030
Sometimes.shawn.the answer is
right in front of your eyes.

543
00:29:12.040 --> 00:29:14.900
You just need to choose to see it.

544
00:29:19.580 --> 00:29:21.150
That was creepy.

545
00:29:21.900 --> 00:29:23.630
Whoa.this is it.Alice's house.

546
00:29:23.640 --> 00:29:24.660
I know there's something here.

547
00:29:24.670 --> 00:29:25.950
I've just got to find it.

548
00:29:26.670 --> 00:29:27.710
Here's the plan.

549
00:29:27.720 --> 00:29:30.210
You ring the doorbell and distract who.

550
00:29:30.220 --> 00:29:32.710
whom. who? Whom?

551
00:29:32.720 --> 00:29:33.880
- Whom...
- the person.

552
00:29:33.890 --> 00:29:34.920
The person that answers the door.

553
00:29:34.930 --> 00:29:36.890
I go around back.figure out a way in.

554
00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:37.700
Are you kidding?

555
00:29:37.710 --> 00:29:39.130
It took the whole ride to come up with that?

556
00:29:39.540 --> 00:29:41.170
Well.feel free to make revisions.gus.

557
00:29:41.180 --> 00:29:42.240
How am I supposed to distract them?

558
00:29:42.250 --> 00:29:43.370
Oh.you'll think of something.

559
00:29:43.380 --> 00:29:44.150
Good luck.

560
00:29:44.160 --> 00:29:45.480
We're all counting on you.

561
00:29:50.750 --> 00:29:51.660
Mrs.Harthan?

562
00:29:51.670 --> 00:29:54.350
No.the harthans are down at the cemetery.

563
00:29:54.360 --> 00:29:56.180
I'm poppy.the housekeeper.

564
00:29:56.190 --> 00:29:57.080
May I help you?

565
00:29:57.090 --> 00:29:58.650
Um.yes.

566
00:29:58.660 --> 00:30:00.170
Have you seen mrs.Pickles?

567
00:30:00.180 --> 00:30:01.600
Mrs.Pickles?

568
00:30:01.610 --> 00:30:04.050
Mrs.Pickles.my orange tabby?

569
00:30:04.060 --> 00:30:05.460
You must have seen her.

570
00:30:05.470 --> 00:30:08.850
She's pregnant with who knows
how many unborn tabby kittens.

571
00:30:09.330 --> 00:30:10.700
and I've lost her!

572
00:30:15.760 --> 00:30:17.100
- You know.
- thank you.

573
00:30:17.110 --> 00:30:20.360
Growing up in edinburgh.my
sisters and i had a basset hound

574
00:30:20.370 --> 00:30:22.100
who used to hoot like a snowy owl.

575
00:30:22.110 --> 00:30:23.240
No kidding?

576
00:30:23.650 --> 00:30:24.750
What'd you name him?

577
00:30:25.360 --> 00:30:27.410
Eh.we called him "basset hound."

578
00:30:27.420 --> 00:30:28.570
Although my.

579
00:30:28.580 --> 00:30:30.560
my sister.she always used
to call him "uncle jimmy."

580
00:30:30.910 --> 00:30:32.550
I never knew why.

581
00:30:37.580 --> 00:30:39.930
Mrs.Pickles!

582
00:30:40.440 --> 00:30:41.370
Oh.dear.

583
00:30:41.380 --> 00:30:44.510
your mrs.Pickles will
come back to you.d'andre.

584
00:31:13.210 --> 00:31:15.570
Doreen and i were closer than sisters.

585
00:31:30.180 --> 00:31:31.800
What in the heaven's that?

586
00:31:32.440 --> 00:31:33.950
I have got to set this thing on vibrate.

587
00:31:34.550 --> 00:31:35.520
I'm sorry.who is this?

588
00:31:35.530 --> 00:31:36.550
Shawn.it's eden.

589
00:31:36.560 --> 00:31:38.340
- Who?
- From beta kappa theta.

590
00:31:38.350 --> 00:31:40.720
Are you coming to our
party.or.like.what the heck?

591
00:31:40.730 --> 00:31:42.330
There are cops here and everything.

592
00:31:42.340 --> 00:31:43.210
Let me talk to mary lou.

593
00:31:43.220 --> 00:31:46.070
Mary lou had to go to some
candlelight vigil thingy for doreen.

594
00:31:46.080 --> 00:31:46.710
Vigil?

595
00:31:47.460 --> 00:31:48.220
What vigil? There was--

596
00:31:48.400 --> 00:31:51.280
yeah.at that creepy
wispy sunny pines place.

597
00:31:54.150 --> 00:31:56.660
Bianca buried it in the
tar pits three nights ago.

598
00:32:00.050 --> 00:32:02.200
what about bud? Can he come?

599
00:32:23.940 --> 00:32:28.290
Has anyone ever told you you look like
little bud from the old cosby show?

600
00:32:29.340 --> 00:32:30.600
Yes.ma'am.but.

601
00:32:30.610 --> 00:32:32.230
I was not bud.

602
00:32:37.050 --> 00:32:38.380
Hello?

603
00:32:38.760 --> 00:32:40.060
Bet.

604
00:32:40.070 --> 00:32:41.130
It's her.

605
00:32:41.140 --> 00:32:41.970
Who?

606
00:32:41.980 --> 00:32:43.040
Mrs.Pickles.

607
00:32:43.050 --> 00:32:44.550
She's home.

608
00:32:47.490 --> 00:32:48.920
- How you going to-
- it was her.

609
00:32:48.930 --> 00:32:49.900
And I've got the "how."

610
00:32:49.910 --> 00:32:51.190
We've got to go to wispy sunny pines.

611
00:32:51.200 --> 00:32:52.970
What? No.no.no.You said
go to the sorority house.

612
00:32:52.980 --> 00:32:54.380
No.the girls are fine.Cops are there.

613
00:32:54.390 --> 00:32:58.200
Meanwhile.juliet's at some candlelight
vigil with doreen's family at the asylum.

614
00:32:58.210 --> 00:33:01.680
Wait a minute.no.no.no.The housekeeper just
said doreen's parents were at the cemetery.

615
00:33:02.180 --> 00:33:03.440
What?

616
00:33:04.910 --> 00:33:06.860
- What?
- Oh.god.

617
00:33:06.870 --> 00:33:07.880
Of course.

618
00:33:07.890 --> 00:33:10.230
Why mess around with the worker
bees when you can kill the queen?

619
00:33:10.240 --> 00:33:11.060
What are you talking about.shawn?

620
00:33:11.070 --> 00:33:12.610
Gus.alice!

621
00:33:12.620 --> 00:33:15.430
She wanted us all at
that party.including us.

622
00:33:15.440 --> 00:33:17.450
so that she could get mary lou by herself!

623
00:33:17.460 --> 00:33:18.990
This is silence of the lambs!

624
00:33:19.290 --> 00:33:21.030
Which means we're both scott glenn!

625
00:33:22.090 --> 00:33:25.320
Okay.shawn.if I'm going to go
back to that creepy-ass institution

626
00:33:25.330 --> 00:33:26.740
I've been afraid to
drive by since I was nine.

627
00:33:26.750 --> 00:33:27.930
there's going to be some
rules and regulations.

628
00:33:27.940 --> 00:33:30.400
- Gus.this is no time for fun-
- listen.shawn!

629
00:33:30.410 --> 00:33:31.650
I will not enter a room first.

630
00:33:31.660 --> 00:33:33.090
I will not enter a room last.

631
00:33:33.100 --> 00:33:34.710
I will not investigate
any suspicious noises.

632
00:33:34.720 --> 00:33:36.270
or go looking for a fuse box.

633
00:33:36.280 --> 00:33:38.040
and you will not.under any circumstance.

634
00:33:38.050 --> 00:33:40.300
leave me by myself
without a weapon of some sort.

635
00:33:40.310 --> 00:33:42.120
Do you understand and agree to my terms?

636
00:33:42.130 --> 00:33:43.100
I'm not prepared to negotiate--

637
00:33:43.110 --> 00:33:44.390
do you understand.shawn?

638
00:33:44.400 --> 00:33:46.140
Yes! I do.yes!

639
00:33:46.150 --> 00:33:46.790
All right.

640
00:33:47.240 --> 00:33:48.590
Let's go help juliet.

641
00:33:57.790 --> 00:33:59.200
Scarecrow.

642
00:33:59.600 --> 00:34:00.550
did we get him?

643
00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:02.710
No.No.of course we didn't get him.

644
00:34:02.720 --> 00:34:06.110
Your little pursuit sort of ended
when you had a mild cardiac arrest.

645
00:34:06.510 --> 00:34:08.530
When were you going to
tell me about the pacemaker?

646
00:34:08.540 --> 00:34:11.320
And how dare you try and
scale a fence in high heels?

647
00:34:11.330 --> 00:34:13.220
He was the victim.goochberg.

648
00:34:13.230 --> 00:34:14.450
But did we get him?

649
00:34:24.530 --> 00:34:26.100
Yeah.we got him.goochberg.

650
00:34:30.290 --> 00:34:31.400
Lassiter.

651
00:34:31.810 --> 00:34:32.650
Spencer?

652
00:34:33.160 --> 00:34:36.850
Do you realize you are the second to last 
human person on this planet I want to be 
speaking to right now?

653
00:35:00.700 --> 00:35:03.080
Call for backup.o'hara.Just make the call.

654
00:35:03.630 --> 00:35:05.170
Better safe than sorry.

655
00:35:08.290 --> 00:35:09.090
Mary lou!

656
00:35:09.540 --> 00:35:11.460
We're.we're over here.

657
00:35:19.070 --> 00:35:21.200
I have to say.I'm a little
shocked to see you here.

658
00:35:21.210 --> 00:35:22.420
Where's everyone else?

659
00:35:22.430 --> 00:35:23.600
Oh.upstairs.

660
00:35:23.610 --> 00:35:25.480
They're waiting for you.

661
00:35:26.160 --> 00:35:27.680
I told them you probably wouldn't show.

662
00:35:27.690 --> 00:35:29.100
Well.maybe you misjudged me.

663
00:35:30.420 --> 00:35:31.760
Maybe I did.

664
00:35:32.700 --> 00:35:33.940
Follow me?

665
00:35:38.110 --> 00:35:39.850
this must have taken hours.

666
00:35:45.430 --> 00:35:48.260
I mean.this is really extensive.

667
00:35:48.760 --> 00:35:50.110
candle-wise.

668
00:35:57.840 --> 00:35:59.970
The whole family's waiting in room 413.

669
00:36:00.030 --> 00:36:01.240
Okay.

670
00:36:21.890 --> 00:36:23.760
Alice.what the hell is this?

671
00:36:25.840 --> 00:36:28.020
Welcome to the party.mary lou.

672
00:36:31.080 --> 00:36:32.890
It's a banquet fit for a queen!

673
00:36:37.340 --> 00:36:38.790
Alice.you do not want to do this.

674
00:36:38.800 --> 00:36:39.670
Give me the ax.

675
00:36:39.680 --> 00:36:41.260
I'm not who you think I am.

676
00:36:42.040 --> 00:36:45.890
No.you are exactly who I think you are.

677
00:36:45.900 --> 00:36:50.010
You're the reason girls vomit
and starve themselves to death.

678
00:36:50.020 --> 00:36:52.970
And you're the reason that
they fill themselves with plastic.

679
00:36:52.980 --> 00:36:56.000
and you are the reason that doreen is dead.

680
00:36:57.110 --> 00:37:02.620
and so now.on behalf of the
entire suit of the broken hearts.

681
00:37:02.960 --> 00:37:05.470
alice will now lop off the queen's head.

682
00:37:10.040 --> 00:37:13.620
That just sounded so much better
out loud than it did in my head.

683
00:37:21.940 --> 00:37:22.740
Lassie!

684
00:37:22.750 --> 00:37:24.800
Our timing is really starting to crackle.

685
00:37:25.170 --> 00:37:26.750
No!

686
00:37:36.380 --> 00:37:37.710
We made a deal.shawn!

687
00:37:38.320 --> 00:37:39.820
Thank you.

688
00:37:53.710 --> 00:37:54.950
Get it out! Get it out!

689
00:37:54.960 --> 00:37:56.060
Pull your foot out of the shoe!

690
00:37:56.070 --> 00:37:57.420
I can't! It's too tight!

691
00:37:57.580 --> 00:37:58.840
Shawn.shawn.don't leave me.shawn.

692
00:37:58.850 --> 00:37:59.820
That was rule number five.

693
00:37:59.830 --> 00:38:00.860
Wiggle your big toe!

694
00:38:00.870 --> 00:38:02.050
I can't wiggle my big toe!

695
00:38:02.060 --> 00:38:02.880
- Dude!
- What?

696
00:38:02.890 --> 00:38:04.220
Work the laces.

697
00:38:04.230 --> 00:38:06.040
Shawn? Shawn!

698
00:38:09.430 --> 00:38:10.890
Jules!

699
00:38:19.870 --> 00:38:21.700
Nope.not tonight.No.

700
00:38:29.640 --> 00:38:30.780
That is it!

701
00:38:30.790 --> 00:38:32.540
Now you die for sure!

702
00:38:32.930 --> 00:38:34.040
I don't think so.

703
00:38:36.180 --> 00:38:40.030
You are under arrest.you
crazy.crazy.crazy bitch!

704
00:38:40.080 --> 00:38:41.620
- Detective!
- Juliet!

705
00:39:01.960 --> 00:39:02.900
I got it.

706
00:39:05.910 --> 00:39:07.190
I got it.

707
00:39:16.030 --> 00:39:17.760
What the hell happened in there?

708
00:39:17.770 --> 00:39:19.330
She's crazy.

709
00:39:19.340 --> 00:39:20.310
She's possessed.

710
00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:21.720
- You have to believe me-
- o'hara?

711
00:39:21.730 --> 00:39:22.910
You're asking me?

712
00:39:22.920 --> 00:39:24.820
I thought I was coming
to a candlelight vigil.

713
00:39:24.830 --> 00:39:27.140
I thought I was coming
to pay my condolences.

714
00:39:27.150 --> 00:39:28.870
Apparently.that wasn't the case.

715
00:39:32.070 --> 00:39:33.590
give me that.

716
00:39:34.170 --> 00:39:35.900
What would you have done.shawn.

717
00:39:37.290 --> 00:39:39.230
if it was your best friend?

718
00:39:41.620 --> 00:39:43.480
What would you have done?

719
00:39:46.570 --> 00:39:47.470
Oh.no.

720
00:39:48.020 --> 00:39:49.360
Gus.

721
00:39:54.690 --> 00:39:57.330
Bud!

722
00:40:00.260 --> 00:40:04.360
Work the laces.

723
00:40:04.700 --> 00:40:06.020
shawn!

724
00:40:06.030 --> 00:40:07.790
Come get me out of here!

725
00:40:08.490 --> 00:40:10.400
That's not funny.shawn!

726
00:40:15.540 --> 00:40:16.930
Did I upset you?

727
00:40:16.980 --> 00:40:18.350
- Upset me?
- Insult you?

728
00:40:18.360 --> 00:40:20.570
Demean you in some way
that I do not comprehend?

729
00:40:21.510 --> 00:40:24.010
Detective.I'm pretty sure I have no
idea what you're talking about.

730
00:40:24.020 --> 00:40:26.550
The woman.The crazy woman?

731
00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:29.430
The half-deaf litigating
nightmare express of a detective.

732
00:40:29.440 --> 00:40:31.940
Why would you put me.of
all people.with her?

733
00:40:31.950 --> 00:40:33.100
I'm head detective.

734
00:40:33.110 --> 00:40:35.130
Honestly.I thought you
two might hit it off.

735
00:40:35.820 --> 00:40:37.190
Why would you possibly think that?

736
00:40:37.200 --> 00:40:39.230
Well.she kind of
reminded me a little of you.

737
00:40:39.240 --> 00:40:40.540
You know.a few years down the road.

738
00:40:40.550 --> 00:40:41.970
Similar interest.outlooks.

739
00:40:42.810 --> 00:40:44.360
everyone thought it
was a pretty good idea.

740
00:40:46.840 --> 00:40:48.650
That's how people perceive me?

741
00:40:50.270 --> 00:40:53.580
We're all a little surprised
that it didn't work out.carlton.

742
00:41:17.650 --> 00:41:19.300
You were dirty.though.

743
00:41:19.670 --> 00:41:21.090
Dirty mother.

744
00:41:26.290 --> 00:41:28.750
Dude.we could hear you
from the fourth floor.

745
00:41:29.080 --> 00:41:31.070
Don't lie! Don't lie!

746
00:41:36.360 --> 00:41:37.540
Hey.lassie!

